<text xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="diplomatic"><body><div type="leaf"><p><pb facs="#f018"/>
                    <metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z058" function="folio" n="17" place="top right margin">folio number 17</metamark>
                </p>
                <p>It were the vilest thing you could say<lb/> of a true American author<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z057" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">
                        <corr change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z057" rend="print">.</corr>
                    </add><corr change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z057" rend="print"/>that he were<lb/>
                    an American <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z056" function="insertion" place="below inline above" rend="caret">caret with
                    guding line</metamark><del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z000" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">Milton</del> <add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z001" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">Tompkins.</add> Call him an American<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z055" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add><lb/>
                    and have done<add change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z054" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline">;</add> <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z002" hand="metadata#HM" rend="multiple-stroke">with it,</del> for you cannot say<lb/> <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z003" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">compliment were better</del> <add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z004" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="no_caret">a nobler thing of him.</add>-But
                    it is<lb/><metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z053" function="insertion" place="margin left" rend="x">x</metamark><add change="metadata#StBa" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z005" hand="metadata#ESM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">
                        <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z005" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">the vilest thing</del>
                    </add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z052" function="insertion" place="below" rend="caret">caret</metamark><add change="metadata#StBa" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z006" hand="metadata#ESM" place="above" rend="no_caret">not meant</add> that all American writers should<lb/><metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z051" function="insertion" place="margin left" rend="no_caret">x</metamark> studiously cleave to <add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z050" hand="metadata#ESM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">nationality </add>in their<lb/> writings<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z049" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">;</add> only this<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z048" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add>
                    no American writer should<lb/> write like an Englishman<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z047" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> or a Frenchman<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z046" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">;</add><lb/>
                    let him write like a man<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z045" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> for then he will
                    be<lb/> sure to write like an American<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z044" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">.</add>
                    Let us<lb/> away with this <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z007" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">Bostonian</del> leaven of <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z008" hand="metadata#ESM" place="above" rend="caret">literary</add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z043" function="insertion" place="inline" rend="caret">caret</metamark><reg change="metadata#StE" facs="#f018_z041 #f018_z042">flunkey-<lb/>ism</reg>
                    towards England<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z040" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">.</add> If either must play<lb/> the
                    flunkey<metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z038" function="insertion" place="inline" rend="caret"/> <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z009" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">in this thing,</add> let England do it<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z036" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> not us<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z035" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">.</add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z037" function="connect" rend="line">connecting
                    line</metamark><del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z010" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">and</del> <lb/><del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z011" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">the time is not far off where circumstances</del><lb/><metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z039" function="correction" place="margin left" rend="x">z</metamark> <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z012" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">may </del><del change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z034" hand="metadata#ESM" rend="single-stroke">en</del><del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z012" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">force </del><metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z033" function="insertion" place="inline" rend="caret">caret</metamark><add change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z032" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">
                        <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z012" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">her</del>
                    </add><del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z012" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke"> to it</del>. While we are rapidly<lb/><metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z031" function="insertion" place="margin left" rend="x">x</metamark> preparing for that <add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z030" hand="metadata#ESM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">political</add> supremacy<lb/> <metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z028" function="insertion" place="margin left" rend="x">x</metamark>among <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z013" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">the</add><metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z027" function="insertion" place="inline" rend="caret">caret</metamark> nations<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z026" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> which <add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z029" hand="metadata#ESM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">prophetically </add>
                    awaits <add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z025" hand="metadata#ESM" place="inspace margin" rend="no_caret">us at</add><lb/> the close of the <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z014" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">part</del> <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z015" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">present</add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z024" function="insertion" place="below" rend="no_caret">caret</metamark>century<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z023" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">;</add> in a literary<lb/> point of view<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z022" hand="metadata#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret">,</add> we are deplorably unprepared<lb/> <add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z016" hand="metadata#HM" place="left" rend="no_caret">for it;</add> and we seem
                    studious to remain so. Hitherto<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z021" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add><lb/> reasons
                    might have existed why this should be<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z020" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">;</add><lb/>
                    but no good reason exists now. And all<lb/> <metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z019" function="correction" place="margin left" rend="x">x</metamark>that
                    is requisite to amendment in this matter<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z016" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add><lb/>
                    is simply this<del change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z018" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">,</del><add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z018" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">:</add> that<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z015" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z017" function="insertion" place="inline above" rend="caret">caret with guiding
                    line</metamark><add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z017" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">while freely acknowledging all excellence, everywhere,</add> we
                    should refrain from<lb/> unduly <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z018" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">keep attering</del> <add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z019" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">lauding</add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z014" function="insertion" place="inline" rend="caret">caret</metamark>foreign
                    writers<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z012" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z013" function="insertion" place="below inline above" rend="caret">caret with guiding line</metamark><del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z019" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">with our</del><reg change="metadata#StE" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z021"/><add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z021" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret"><reg change="metadata#StE" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z021">&amp;, </reg>at the same time,</add><lb/> <del change="metadata#StBa" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z021" hand="metadata#ESM" rend="single-stroke">praises</del> <add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z023" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="no_caret">
                        <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z023" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">bravos</del>
                    </add><del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z024" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">and</del> duly <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z011" function="insertion" place="below inline above" rend="caret">caret with guiding line</metamark><del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z025" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">rewarding</del> <add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z026" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">recognise<del change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z010" hand="metadata#HM" rend="multi-stroke">ing</del></add> the meritorious<lb/><metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z009" function="correction" place="margin left" rend="x">x</metamark> writers that are our own<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z008" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">;--</add>those writers<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z007" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add>
                    who<lb/> breathe that unshackled<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z006" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> democratic spirit <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z005" function="insertion" place="inline above" rend="caret">caret with guiding line</metamark><add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z027" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">of Christianity</add><lb/><metamark change="metadata#StB" facs="#f018_z004" function="insertion" place="margin left" rend="x">x</metamark> in all things<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z003" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z028" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">that</del> <add change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z029" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">which</add> <metamark change="metadata#StC" facs="#f018_z002" function="insertion" place="inline" rend="caret">caret</metamark>now takes
                    the<metamark change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z001" function="insertion" place="below inline" rend="caret">caret</metamark> <add change="metadata#StBa" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z030" hand="metadata#ESM" place="above" rend="caret">practical</add> lead<lb/> in
                    th<add change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z000" hand="metadata#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">is</add><del change="metadata#StBa" facs="#f018_z000" hand="metadata##HM" rend="single-stroke">e</del> world,
                    though <del change="metadata#StC" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f018_z031" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">led by us</del> at the same</p>
            </div>

